      },
      "lineNbr": 42,
      "author": {
        "id": 1000042
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-08-21T04:24:57Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "i\u0027m using this for unit tests in a helper package: https://user.git.corp.google.com/derat/tast/+/master/src/chromiumos/tast/common/runner/runner_test.go#24\n\ni\u0027m not sure what the conventions are (if any) about exporting test-only functions in go. i really dislike having these singleton members, but i couldn\u0027t come up with any other way to allow tests to register themselves from init functions -- here\u0027s what test registration looks like right now: https://user.git.corp.google.com/derat/tast/+/master/src/chromiumos/tast/local/tests/example/fail.go#11\n\nthinking about it more, i suppose i could keep the singleton variables here but instead initialize them from outside this package, e.g. by adding a SetGlobalRegistry(reg *Registry) function (and perhaps moving the error list into the Registry struct, which may make more sense in any case). does that feel cleaner to you?",
      "parentUuid": "8bd8a5d8_5ded2137",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 42,
        "startChar": 5,
        "endLine": 42,
        "endChar": 20
      },
      "revId": "286a109cb982d4ad87a4fb8c338a071f00b99744",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
